            "questionText": "A sports scientist is analyzing an athlete's vertical jump. The athlete has a mass of $!$70\\text{ kg}$!$. On Earth, the gravitational field strength is $!$9.8\\text{ N/kg}$!$, and on Mars, it is $!$3.7\\text{ N/kg}$!$. Calculate the difference in the athlete's weight (in $!$\\text{N}$!$) between Earth and the simulated Martian environment.",
